:INFO
The Victorian Heroine Who Refuses to Be Made Small
Jane Eyre was published in 1847 under the male pseudonym Currer Bell and it is \
the most fierce portrait of female refusal in the English literary canon. Jane \
is poor, plain, and dependent, and she spends the entire novel declining to let \
any of those conditions determine who she is or what she is worth. The novel \
is not without its problems, particularly in the treatment of Bertha Mason, \
but Jane herself remains one of the most alive characters in any novel I have read.

